An expression meaning "to make a mistake." Derived from the quote by [[Horace]]: "Even the worthy Homer sometimes nods."[http://www.thinkexist.com/English/Author/x/Author_3120_9.htm]

Poet [[Alexander Pope]] expanded on his theme: "Those oft are stratagems which errors seem, Nor is it Homer nods, but we that dream."[http://www.giga-usa.com/quotes/authors/alexander_pope_a008.htm] 

Used by Wall Street Journal's [[James Taranto]] to indicate the correction of a mistake.[http://www.opinionjournal.com/best/]

